RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELAWARE PARK RACE 1 1M 70Y Dirt CR: 48. Maiden Claiming Purse 10000. (PLUS UP TO 50% Other Sources) FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. Claiming Price $6,250, if for $5,000, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MR LAOBAN raced mid-pack three wide and outside into and on the first turn, advanced willingly up the backstretch, took the lead by the three-eighths, was asked for more at the top of the stretch, geared down through the final sixteenth. FINN'S POINT got away well, was joint leader heading to the first turn, eased back ceding the lead content to rate in the two path, moved out four wide leaving the backstretch, put to urging on the far turn, swung six wide into upper stretch, fought on to get the place while no threat to the winner. SETTE STELLE was unhurried at the back racing inside, went in the four path on the far turn still far back, angled out in mid-stretch, kicked on mildly. NATURE OFTHE BEAST was taken under a hold early racing mid-pack inside saving ground, made a swift advance up the backstretch inside to reach striking distance, swung out five wide turning for home, lacked the needed late kick. CAPT COMPLICATED moved forward outside on the first turn, took the lead and cleared on the first turn while shifting in, set the tempo near the inside up the backstretch, was overtaken early on the far turn, faded. EL GRAN CUYAYA raced outside at the back early, advanced four wide and outside into the far turn, faltered and faded.

ENTRY.NAME: Finn's Point
ENTRY.COMMENT: ceded lead, rated 2p, angled 4wd 7/16, swung 6w, got 2nd

ENTRY.NAME: Nature Ofthe Beast
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated insd early, rail advance bkstr, swung 5w, no late kick

ENTRY.NAME: Sette Stelle
ENTRY.COMMENT: unhurried at rear inside, 4p 2nd turn, angled out mid-str, mildly

ENTRY.NAME: Mr Laoban
ENTRY.OWNER: Kernan Jr Morris E and Jagger Inc
ENTRY.COMMENT: 3wd advance, led by 3/8, ask top str, gear down 1/16

ENTRY.NAME: El Gran Cuyaya
ENTRY.COMMENT: outside at rear early, advanced 4w, faltered

ENTRY.NAME: Capt Complicated
ENTRY.COMMENT: moved forward & clear, pace, near inside, faded

RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELAWARE PARK RACE 2 1M Dirt CR: 69. Claiming Purse 16000. (PLUS UP TO 50% Other Sources) FOR FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD OR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE AUGUST 9, 2022. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since July 9, 2023 Allowed 3 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500, For Each $2,500 To $7,500 2 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $6,250 Or Less Not Considered In Estimating Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LUCKY LORRAINE raced five to six wide and outside throughout while just off the pace, moved nearer to challenge for the lead in upper stretch, lost the crop about the sixteenth pole then edged past late. MATOULA was mildly coaxed from the break, moved clear early, dictated the pace racing well removed from the rail in the two to three path then three to four path up the backstretch, drifted out a bit turning into upper stretch, was put to urging at the top of the lane, challenged by an outside foe in mid-stretch and outfinished. SHAOLIN was within range four to five wide stalking the leader, put to urging past the quarter pole, shifted inside the leader in upper stretch, lacked the needed late kick. PRUSSIAN BLUE settled outside a foe at the back, went two to three wide on the far turn, was no threat to the top three. RATIONALMILLENNIAL was within range three to four wide, dropped back and faded. SIRENETTA saved ground to no avail.

ENTRY.COMMENT: in range 3-4w, faded

ENTRY.NAME: Matoula
ENTRY.OWNER: Lo Charles Johnson Troy and Lee John M
ENTRY.COMMENT: coax brk, clear, 2-4p, pace, drift into str, outfinished

ENTRY.NAME: Shaolin

ENTRY.NAME: Lucky Lorraine
ENTRY.OWNER: Mary E Eppler Racing Stable Inc and Shooting Star Racing Stables LLC
ENTRY.COMMENT: 5-6w trip, lost crop 1/16, edged past foe late

RACE.FOOTNOTES: GILDED GHOST settled off the early leader outside a foe three deep, advanced up the backstretch willingly taking the lead three furlongs out, asked for more at the three-sixteenths, was just flagged inside the final furlong and geared down the final sixteenth. ALLIE'S HALO raced four to five wide early, made a mild advance early up the backstretch, shifted in soon after, advanced inside a rival on the far turn, was no match for the winner. LIFESAWINDINGROAD stumbled badly at the start spotting the field about seven lengths, brought up the rear, raced quite wide on the second turn while advancing five to six deep, lacked the needed late kick. PAUL'S TRICKY TALE settled well back racing inside, failed to menace. LILLI ROSE keenly moved clear setting the pace off the rail under restraint from the rider, was overtaken three furlongs out, drifted out in upper stretch, tired.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: YOU'RE THE ONE attended then prompted the pace from outside, took a narrow lead at the five-sixteenths, was asked for more by upper stretch, responded to draw away. SEA ART stalked from outside a foe off the leading pair, raced mostly three to four wide, was no match for the winner but secured the place. BIG AMBITION was outsprinted in the early going racing outside, went three to four deep through the turn, swung six wide into upper stretch, got up for show honors. WINKIWINKI was quick to the lead, set the pace off the rail, moved nearer the fence into the turn and was pressured by the winner, gave way. CHILD PROOF tracked from inside a rival off the leading pair, failed to menace. FABULOUS CANDY was very hard to load, broke a step slowly, was never a threat.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELAWARE PARK RACE 5 1M 70Y Dirt CR: 82. Maiden Special Weight Purse 38000. (PLUS UP TO 50% Other Sources) FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. Horses which have not started for less than $32,000 have preference. Horses which have started for less than $32,000 and have since finished 2nd, 3rd Or 4th for $32,000 or more have same preference. (Rail at 30 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BROOKLYN GIRL was urged at the start, gained forward position stalking four wide, dropped back on the far turn, asked for more by the quarter, floated out a few paths turning for home, kept on and surged late to just get up. EVITA was caught five to six wide through the first turn, advanced mildly up the backstretch, gradually shifted in on the far turn, made the rail at the quarter pole, bid inside in late stretch but missed. SERGEANT MOLLY broke alertly and quickly moved clear to set the pace racing off the rail in three path, turned back an inside challenger midway on the far turn, spurted clear by the quarter pole, drifted out turning for home, began to shorten stride and drifted in then out in mid- to late-stretch, was outfinished. TREASURED GEM broke outwardly and was also forced out a bit, bumping a rival at the start, rated just in behind the leader inside, moved up early on the far turn, made a mild bid coming to within half a length of the leader from the inside but in the two path and put to urging at the five-sixteenths, was promptly turned back, kept on in the stretch and loomed a late threat but needed more. COMPASS RISES settled in the four to five path in the back half of the field, passed foes on the far turn coming into upper stretch five to six wide, ran on mostly one-paced but with mild late interest. KAKE'S TAP DANCER was bumped at the start, settled mid-pack inside early, faded in the lane. GUN RUNNIN' GAL was reluctant to load, caught seven wide into the first turn taking back and shifting in on that bend but still racing deep out on the course in behind foes, fanned out again on the far turn still about mid-pack, failed to rally. INCLUDE THE MUNNY was urged at the start, chased briefly five then four wide steadily dropping back early up the backstretch. INVEST WISELY stumbled a bit outwardly at the start, was not a threat.

ENTRY.COMMENT: stumbled start, no threat

RACE.FOOTNOTES: VALUABLE BREIGH moved five then four wide on the turn taking command, drew clear in the stretch while drifting in. CARTWHEEL unhurriedly brought up the rear, swung ten wide into upper stretch, was no match but second best. RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELAWARE PARK RACE 7 5F Dirt CR: 88. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 39000. (PLUS UP TO 50% Other Sources) FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OR RESTRICTED OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $28,000. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; O lder, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since July 9, 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since May 9, 2023 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $28,000 (Maiden, Claiming, And Starter Races Not Considered In Estimating Allowances). (If deemed inadvisable by management not t o run this race over the turf course, it will be run on the main track at Five Furlongs) (Rail at 30 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SHERO moved forward into the turn dueling early on that bend, took a narrow lead at the five-sixteenths, edged clear in upper stretch then extended the margin, was in hand very late once safely in front. BOUND BY DESTINY was urged at the break but outsprinted early, raced off the inside about in the four path on the turn and trailing, kept on to get up for second. R AVERIE LYNN was hard to load, broke sharply and was quickly clear to set the pace, raced off the rail, was engaged and dueled through the turn, weakened in the stretch.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELAWARE PARK RACE 8 1M Dirt CR: 83. Claiming Purse 14000. (PLUS UP TO 50% Other Sources) FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE FEBRUARY 9, 2023 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since July 9, 2023 Allowe d 2 lbs. A Race Since May 9, 2023 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000 (Races Where Entered For $4,000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility And Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CAMP PENDLETON was caught four to five wide in the early going while forwardly-positioned, stalked from outside into the far turn caught wide again, eased back and angled in cutting the corner past the quarter pole, bid inside, dueled late and held that rival. NIGHT OPS was caught widest into the first turn but able to move in a path from five to four wide on that bend, pressed up the backstretch going three to four wide on the far turn, contended for the lead in upper- to mid-stretch, dueled late but was second best. TINY TIN moved quick to the lead setting the pace from off the rail, pressured up the backstretch, contended till the lane but was outkicked. LIFESPAN switched off the rail in the early going racing in the two then three path on the first turn, settled in behind the leaders, floated nine wide into upper stretch and gaining, loomed a threat at the furlong grounds but could not sustain the effort and evened out. MELINA'S DREAM was outpaced racing inside, fanned six wide into upper stretch and passed tired foes. UNDERDOG was coaxed forward, raced three wide in range of the leader early, moved four wide into the far turn making a bid near the quarter pole, drifted out numerous paths leaving that bend, weakened in the stretch. COSMIC TREASURE was in tight on the rail entering the first turn, raced near the inside off the lead, failed to rally. FEARLESS FLY raced outside at the rear in the three to four path early, failed to menace.
